  <Name>k__BackingField: Obadiah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: oba
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: "Edom\u2019s Judgment Announced"
      content: "  This is the vision that the Sovereign <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        revealed to Obadiah concerning the land of Edom.We have heard a message from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>that an ambassador was sent to the nations
        to say,\u201CGet ready, everyone!Let\u2019s assemble our armies and attack
        Edom!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to Edom,\u201CI will cut you
        down to size among the nations;you will be greatly despised.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have been deceived by your own pridebecause you live in a rock
        fortressand make your home high in the mountains.\u2018Who can ever reach
        us way up here?\u2019you ask boastfully.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But even if you soar as high as eaglesand build your nest among the
        stars,I will bring you crashing down,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CIf thieves came at night and robbed you(what a disaster awaits
        you!),they would not take everything.Those who harvest grapesalways leave
        a few for the poor.But your enemies will wipe you out completely!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Every nook and cranny of Edom[[COMMENT(0)]]will be searched and looted.Every
        treasure will be found and taken.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:6 '
        content: Hebrew <b>Esau; </b>also in 8b, 9, 18, 19, 21.
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CAll your allies will turn against you.They will help to chase
        you from your land.They will promise you peacewhile plotting to deceive and
        destroy you.Your trusted friends will set traps for you,and you won\u2019t
        even know about it.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At that time not a single wise personwill be left in the whole land
        of Edom,\u201Dsays the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201CFor on the mountains
        of EdomI will destroy everyone who has understanding.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Reasons for Edom\u2019s Punishment"
      content: 'The mightiest warriors of Temanwill be terrified,and everyone on
        the mountains of Edomwill be cut down in the slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBecause of the violence you didto your close relatives in Israel,[[COMMENT(0)]]you
        will be filled with shameand destroyed forever.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: "Hebrew <b>your brother Jacob. </b>The names \u201CJacob\u201D and
          \u201CIsrael\u201D are often interchanged throughout the Old Testament,
          referring sometimes to the individual patriarch and sometimes to the nation."
    - title: 
      content: "When they were invaded,you stood aloof, refusing to help them.Foreign
        invaders carried off their wealthand cast lots to divide up Jerusalem,but
        you acted like one of Israel\u2019s enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CYou should not have gloatedwhen they exiled your relatives
        to distant lands.You should not have rejoicedwhen the people of Judah suffered
        such misfortune.You should not have spoken arrogantlyin that terrible time
        of trouble.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You should not have plundered the land of Israelwhen they were suffering
        such calamity.You should not have gloated over their destructionwhen they
        were suffering such calamity.You should not have seized their wealthwhen
        they were suffering such calamity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Edom Destroyed, Israel Restored
      content: 'You should not have stood at the crossroads,killing those who tried
        to escape.You should not have captured the survivorsand handed them over
        in their terrible time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThe day is near when I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,will
        judge all godless nations!As you have done to Israel,so it will be done to
        you.All your evil deedswill fall back on your own heads.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just as you swallowed up my peopleon my holy mountain,so you and
        the surrounding nationswill swallow the punishment I pour out on you.Yes,
        all you nations will drink and staggerand disappear from history.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CBut Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] will become a refuge for those
        who escape;it will be a holy place.And the people of Israel[[COMMENT(1)]]
        will come backto reclaim their inheritance.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17a '
        content: Hebrew <b>Mount Zion.</b>
      - number: '1:17b '
        content: Hebrew <b>house of Jacob; </b>also in 18. See note on 10.
    - title: 
      content: 'The people of Israel will be a raging fire,and Edom a field of dry
        stubble.The descendants of Joseph will be a flameroaring across the field,
        devouring everything.There will be no survivors in Edom.I, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        have spoken!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThen my people living in the Negevwill occupy the mountains
        of Edom.Those living in the foothills of Judah[[COMMENT(0)]]will possess
        the Philistine plainsand take over the fields of Ephraim and Samaria.And
        the people of Benjaminwill occupy the land of Gilead.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: Hebrew <b>the Shephelah.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'The exiles of Israel will return to their landand occupy the Phoenician
        coast as far north as Zarephath.The captives from Jerusalem exiled in the
        north[[COMMENT(0)]]will return home and resettle the towns of the Negev.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: Hebrew <b>in Sepharad.</b>
